text.tspan: Super Mario Scralaxy - 0.6.9
This update focuses on gameplay mechanics and ease of
level making!
NEW FEATURES (new objects can be found in the test room)
-Improved the level editor. It includes editing level
progression and the UI is completely redesigned. You can
start the editor by holding E when clicking the green flag.
-Changed back some of the planned scralaxies
-Exploration stages! You have to collect 5 silver stars in
them, and a star appears afterwards! The star's Alt 4 is used.
-Now the physics mode isn't automatically set to Dynamic
-Introduced red coins (there will be 4 in each level)
-Can now place hidden blocks
-Extended the ScreenParameters list's maximum value
-Now checkpoints are physical objects
-Including flip blocks, donut blocks and on-off blocks, new
types of blocks have been added
-Can now place firebars of different lengths
-Enhanced the pause menu slightly
GRAPHICS
-Ground replaced by pipes in some levels
-enemy sprites are more expressive
-Removed eye shines from most sprites, such as stars:
-This makes the game's artstyle more consistent
-Closer to misteryfox13's style, as well as Paper Mario
-Most sprites gain potential to be more expressive.
LEVELS
-The following levels have been remade:
-The Underground: underground section replaced
-Mine Cart Mayhem: changed layout, added springs
-Bowser Jr's Flying Ship: now feels more like a flying ship
I might redo some more levels in the future.
SOUND
-Every character now has a sound effect used when falling
into a bottomless pit.
BUGFIXES
-Fixed the bug where the game would sometimes think the
player was in a pipe, and get softlocked forever
-Fixed objects sometimes not spawning in
(thanks to Hasanmajid10 for the fix)
-Fixed non-scrolling stages failing to put the player at the
start of the level after death
KNOWN BUGS
-The Star Select screen sometimes transitions to the level
too quickly; stars also float out of the screen after a while
-Flip switches don't work with Waluigi's ground pound, and
change state continuously
TO DO
-New levels and mechanics
-Polish bosses
-Add prankster comets
-Add the remaining levels, bosses and some minigames
-Redo the objectives. They should be harder to find, more
specific and mapped to things that don't already have a
reward in-game. (example: find a secret room in the castle)
-Tweak credits sequences
-Add back partners that you can buy? When you press a
button they perform an action (akin to a potion in
MINECRAFT?)
-Fill in Super Mario Scralaxy history book
-Fill HALL OF FAME room
-Improve cutscene (allude to master with small
drawing/anims)
-New characters?
-Save settings to save code
-Fix diving into water backwards bug (x velocity reverses)
-Fix general darkness/forest effect bugginess
-Make parallax background widescreen-friendly
